The conditional distribution of the reward at time $n+1$ given the history and the next action is determined by the environment kernel $\nu$. This follows from the independence of the reward streams: the reward for action $A_{n+1}$ is drawn from the stream at index $k = \text{count}(H_n, A_{n+1})$. Crucially, the history $H_n$ and the action $A_{n+1}$ only depend on stream values at indices strictly less than $k$ (for action $A_{n+1}$), so the variable $R_{n+1} = \omega.2(k, A_{n+1})$ is independent of $(H_n, A_{n+1})$ conditional on $A_{n+1}$.

